<subSubSection id="C33D653B130CA603FF21C33073E0FA7E" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9836B0130CA603FF21C330737EFC9E" blockId="10.[192,630,867,891]" box="[192,630,867,891]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FF21C330737EFC9E" authority="Evans, 1952" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[192,630,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="borax" subSpecies="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FF21C33070D4FC9E" box="[192,476,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Bungalotis borax lactos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B41130CA603FE00C337737EFC9E" author="Evans, W. H." box="[481,630,867,891]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9836B0130CA603FF11C3F773E0FA7E" blockId="10.[192,1441,931,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B41130CA603FF11C3F7709AFC5E" author="Evans, W. H." box="[240,402,931,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans (1952)</bibRefCitation>
described this taxon, based upon a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F3307620130CA603FBBBC3F77591FC5E" box="[1114,1177,932,955]" name="Peru" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Peru</collectingCountry>
, as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FA64C3F7700DFC3E" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borax">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FA64C3F7700DFC3E" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. borax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where it has subsequently languished (Mielke 2004, 2005). Obvious differences between the two taxa in the genitalia illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B41130CA603FD90C3B7721BFC1E" author="Evans, W. H." box="[625,787,995,1019]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans (1952)</bibRefCitation>
and shown herein (
<figureCitation id="131C2A35130CA603FBE6C3B0758CFC1E" box="[1031,1156,995,1019]" captionStart="Figure 89-92" captionStartId="19.[195,279,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,591,1695]" captionTargetId="figure-280@19.[192,1443,570,1698]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 89-92. Male genitalia of Bungalotis (from BRAZIL: Rondônia, unless noted otherwise). Structures shown are lateral, dorsal, and ventral views of tegumen, uncus, gnathos, and associated structures; lateral internal view of right valva; lateral view of aedeagus and associated structures; and ventral view of transtilla and juxta. 89) B. gagarini (GTA 1617). 90) B. astylos (GTA 3166); variation of valvae, a. (GTA 3189, flattened), b. (GTA  3166, flattened). 91) B. lactos (GTA 3062); variation of valvae, a. (GTA 7196), b. (GTA 4133), c. (GTA 7914), all including flattened view of caudal end of valva. 92) B. borax (GTA 7866), including flattened view of caudal end of valva." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532843/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 91-92</figureCitation>
) indicate that they are separate species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FE20C457734DFBFE" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[449,581,1027,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="borax" subSpecies="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FE20C457734DFBFE" box="[449,581,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. b. lactos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here raised to species-level status. This had been suggested (de Jong 1983), but no action was taken. This status for 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FD1DC477726CFBDE" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[764,868,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FD1DC477726CFBDE" box="[764,868,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. lactos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unequivocally verified by finding 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FADBC47774A8FBDE" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[1338,1440,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borax">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FADBC47774A8FBDE" box="[1338,1440,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. borax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FE9AC41770E8FBBE" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[379,480,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FE9AC41770E8FBBE" box="[379,480,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. lactos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in central Rondônia. Differences between the genitalia of the specimen in Evans’ (1952) figure and the genitalia illustrated herein from Rondônia (
<figureCitation id="131C2A35130CA603FC2DC4307516FB9E" box="[972,1054,1123,1147]" captionStart="Figure 89-92" captionStartId="19.[195,279,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,591,1695]" captionTargetId="figure-280@19.[192,1443,570,1698]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 89-92. Male genitalia of Bungalotis (from BRAZIL: Rondônia, unless noted otherwise). Structures shown are lateral, dorsal, and ventral views of tegumen, uncus, gnathos, and associated structures; lateral internal view of right valva; lateral view of aedeagus and associated structures; and ventral view of transtilla and juxta. 89) B. gagarini (GTA 1617). 90) B. astylos (GTA 3166); variation of valvae, a. (GTA 3189, flattened), b. (GTA  3166, flattened). 91) B. lactos (GTA 3062); variation of valvae, a. (GTA 7196), b. (GTA 4133), c. (GTA 7914), all including flattened view of caudal end of valva. 92) B. borax (GTA 7866), including flattened view of caudal end of valva." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532843/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
) may be due to individual variation, these most prevalent in the configuration of the caudal end of the harpe. Male 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FB69C4D775E4FB7E" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1160,1260,1155,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FB69C4D775E4FB7E" box="[1160,1260,1155,1179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. lactos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Rondônia (mean FW length = 
<quantity id="4CDF9B55130CA603FE50C4F07313FB5E" box="[433,539,1187,1211]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.91" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="29.1">29.1 mm</quantity>
[28.1-30.1, n = 4]) vary from pale to dark tawny-brown; the contrast of the paler areas adjacent to the discal macules on both wings depends upon the darkness of the ground color. The costa of the hindwing is more broadly black than on 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FC60C4B772E1FB1E" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[897,1001,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borax">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FC60C4B772E1FB1E" box="[897,1001,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">B. borax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the macules on both wings are broader. That in the discal cell of the forewing has its distal edge in line with the proximal edge of the macule in CuA1-CuA2. The discal series of macules on the forewing is more or less aligned (distal edges) with the macule in CuA1-CuA2 noticeably broader than the others. The venter is similar to the dorsum and the macules on the ventral hindwing vary from vague with pale centers to distinct and enclosed within a narrow, but prominent, brown band.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D653B130CA603FF11C5F073F2FA1E" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9836B0130CA603FF11C5F073F2FA1E" blockId="10.[192,1441,931,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C274D33130CA603FF11C5F070CFFA5E" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[240,455,1443,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bungalotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactos">
<emphasis id="B953EAA2130CA603FF11C5F070CFFA5E" box="[240,455,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Bungalotis lactos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare at Cacaulândia, with two records in June and one each in August and October. These records extend the known distribution of the species eastward; the species had been recorded only in 
<collectingCountry id="F3307620130CA603FE8EC5B770A2FA1E" box="[367,426,1508,1531]" name="Peru" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B41130CA603FE58C5B07342FA1E" author="Evans, W. H." box="[441,586,1507,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans 1952</bibRefCitation>
, Lamas 1994).
</paragraph>
